---
/**
 * idempotency-keys-deep-dive · Figure 4 — fingerprint compare (Level 3).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/idempotency-keys-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). The two arrowhead markers it references
 * (#arwG, #arwA via marker-end="url(#…)") are inlined here in a local <defs> so
 * they resolve standalone (verbatim from the source's hidden top-of-body defs).
 * Lives as an .astro component because raw inline SVG with kebab-case attrs is
 * unreliable inside MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 190"
        role="img"
        aria-label="On every repeat compare the stored fingerprint to the incoming request: match means genuine retry apply section one logic; differ means key misuse reject with 400"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="180"
                y="12"
                width="200"
                height="40"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="31"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">repeat with same key</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="45" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >compare hash(body) to stored fingerprint</text
            >
            <path d="M 230 52 L 150 96" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></path>
            <text x="120" y="80" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a" font-weight="700">matches</text>
            <rect x="20" y="98" width="220" height="58" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="130"
                y="120"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#244a2e">genuine retry of same op</text
            >
            <text x="130" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >→ apply §1: return saved / 409 in-progress</text
            >
            <path d="M 330 52 L 410 96" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <text x="430" y="80" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417" font-weight="700">differs</text>
            <rect x="320" y="98" width="220" height="58" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="430"
                y="120"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a2218">client is misusing the key</text
            >
            <text x="430" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >→ reject 400 (Stripe). Never replay wrong result.</text
            >
            <text
                x="280"
                y="180"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                fill="#1f3a5a"
                font-weight="700"
                >one key names one specific operation — the server enforces the contract</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The fingerprint turns the key into a <em>contract</em>: reuse a key with different
        parameters and the server rejects it rather than silently returning the first request's
        response.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
